d the Making of Fascist Slovakia|title-link=Priest, Politician, Collaborator |date=2013|location=Ithaca |publisher=[[Cornell University Press]] |isbn=978-0-8014-6812-4 |language=en |ref=harv}}\n{{refend}}\n\n====Book chapters====\n{{refbegin|35em|indent=yes}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Bazyler |first1=Michael J.|authorlink=Michael Bazyler |last2=Boyd |first2=Kathryn Lee |last3=Nelson |first3=Kristen L. |last4=Shah |first4=Rajika L. |title=Searching for Justice after the Holocaust: Fulfilling the Terezin Declaration and Immovable Property Restitution |date=2019 |isbn=978-0-19-092306-8 |pages=401\u2013413 |ref={{sfnref|Bazyler et al.|2019}} |language=English |chapter=Slovakia|location=New York|publisher=Oxford University Press}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Dreyfus |first1=Jean-Marc|authorlink=Jean-Marc Dreyfus |last2=Ni\u017e\u0148ansk\u00fd |first2=Eduard|author2link=Eduard Ni\u017e\u0148ansk\u00fd  |editor1-last=Kosmala |editor1-first=Beate |editor2-last=Verbeeck |editor2-first=Georgi |title=Facing the Catastrophe: Jews and non-Jews in Europe during World War II |date=2011 |publisher=Berg |location=Oxford |isbn=978-1-84520-471-6 |language=en |chapter=Jews and non-Jews in the Aryanization Process: Comparison of France and the Slovak State, 1939\u201345|ref=harv}}\n*{{cite conference|last=Fatran|first=Gila|chapter=The Struggle for Jewish Survival during the Holocaust |pp=141\u2013162|editor1-last=D\u0142ugoborski|editor1-first=Wac\u0142aw|editor2-last=T\u00f3th |editor2-first=Dezider |editor3-last=Teresa|editor3-first=\u015awiebocka|editor4-last=Mensfelt|editor4-first=Jarek|translator-last=Mensfeld|translator-first=Jarek|title=The Tragedy of the Jews of Slovakia 1938\u20131945: Slovakia and the \"Final Solution of the Jewish Question\"|origyear=1992 |date =2002|publisher=[[Auschwitz-Birkenau State Museum]] and [[Museum of the Slovak National Uprising]]|location= O\u015bwi\u0119cim and Bansk\u00e1 Bystrica |language=en|ref=harv|isbn=978-83-88526-15-2}}\n*{{cite book|editor1-first=Jaroslava|editor1-last= Rogu\u013eov\u00e1|editor2-first= Maro\u0161 |editor2-last=Hertel  |last1=Hradsk\u00e1 |first1=Katar\u00edna |chapter=Dislok\u00e1cie \u017didov z Bratislavy na jese\u0148 1941 |title=Adepti Moci a \u00faspechu. Etablovanie El\u00edt V Modern\u00fdch Dejin\u00e1ch |date=2016 |pages=315\u2013324 |url=http://forumhistoriae.sk/documents/10180/1832590/bystricky-adepti-moci-a-uspechu.pdf#page=315 |trans-chapter=The Displacement of Jews from Bratislava in Autumn 1941|trans-title=Candidates for Power and Success. Formation of Elites in Modern History |language=sk |isbn=978-80-224-1503-3|ref=harv|publisher={{ill|Forum Historiae|sk}} ([[Slovak Academy of Sciences]])|location=Bratislava}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hutzelmann |first1=Barbara |editor1-last=Bajohr |editor1-first=Frank |editor2-last=L\u00f6w |editor2-first=Andrea |title=The Holocaust and European Societies: Social Processes and Social Dynamics |date=2016|location=London |publisher=Springer |isbn=978-1-137-56984-4 |pages=167\u2013185 |language=en |chapter=Slovak Society and the Jews: Attitudes and Patterns of Behaviour |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hutzelmann |first1=Barbara |editor1-last=Hutzelmann |editor1-first=Barbara|editor2-last=Hausleitner |editor2-first=Mariana |editor3-last=Hazan  |editor3-first=Souzana|title=Slowakei, Rum\u00e4nien und Bulgarien|trans-title=Slovakia, Romania, and Bulgaria |date=2018 |publisher=[[De Gruyter]] |location=Munich |isbn=978-3-11-049520-1 |language=de| series=[[Die Verfolgung und Ermordung der europ\u00e4ischen Juden durch das nationalsozialistische Deutschland 1933-1945]] [The Persecution and Murder of European Jews by Nazi Germany 1933-1945]|volume=13 |chapter=Einf\u00fchrung: Slowakei |trans-chapter=Introduction: Slovakia|ref=harv|pp=18\u201345}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Kamenec |first1=Ivan|chapter=The Slovak state, 1939\u20131945 |editor1-last=Teich |editor1-first=Mikul\u00e1\u0161 |editorlink=Mikul\u00e1\u0161 Teich|editor2-last=Kov\u00e1\u010d |editor2-f