e-crisis |archive-date=15 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> the [[European Union]] by 13 March continued to reject the idea of suspending the [[Schengen Area|Schengen free travel area]] and introducing border controls with Italy.<ref name=\"dw-schengen\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.dw.com/en/coronavirus-eu-rules-out-schengen-border-closures-amid-italy-outbreak/a-52497811 |title=Coronavirus: EU rules out Schengen border closures amid Italy outbreak |date=24 February 2020 |publisher=Deutsche Welle |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200313142436/https://www.dw.com/en/coronavirus-eu-rules-out-schengen-border-closures-amid-italy-outbreak/a-52497811 |archive-date=13 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/opinion/articles/2020-02-25/salvini-and-le-pen-don-t-have-a-european-coronavirus-cure |title=Salvini and Le Pen Don't Have a Coronavirus Cure |date=25 February 2020 |work=Bloomberg |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227122244/https://www.bloomberg.com/opinion/articles/2020-02-25/salvini-and-le-pen-don-t-have-a-european-coronavirus-cure |archive-date=27 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/coronavirus-europe-open-borders-eu-italy-france-britain-germany-spain-a9362536.html |title=Coronavirus: Europe's open borders threatened by spread of disease |date=28 February 2020 |work=The Independent |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317173409/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/coronavirus-europe-open-borders-eu-italy-france-britain-germany-spain-a9362536.html |archive-date=17 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.euractiv.com/section/justice-home-affairs/news/commission-chief-warns-against-unilateral-virus-travel-bans/ |title=Commission chief warns against unilateral virus travel bans |date=13 March 2020 |work=[[EURACTIV]] |access-date=18 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318195056/https://www.euractiv.com/section/justice-home-affairs/news/commission-chief-warns-against-unilateral-virus-travel-bans/ |archive-date=18 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> The deputy leader of the Swiss [[Ticino League]], Lorenzo Quadri, by 29 February had criticised the decision: \"It is alarming that the dogma of wide-open borders is considered a priority.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/26/world/europe/coronavirus-european-union.html |title=Coronavirus Nightmare Could Be the End for Europe's Borderless Dream |date=26 February 2020 |work=The New York Times |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303055756/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/26/world/europe/coronavirus-european-union.html |archive-date=3 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> United States President [[Donald Trump]] said by 12 March the European Union had \"failed to take the same precautions and restrict travel from China and other hot spots\" as the US had implemented.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-usa-trump/trump-suspends-all-travel-from-europe-to-the-united-states-to-fight-coronavirus-idUSKBN20Z04U |title=In dramatic step, Trump restricts travel from Europe to US to fight coronavirus |date=12 March 2020 |agency=Reuters |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314140433/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-usa-trump/trump-suspends-all-travel-from-europe-to-the-united-states-to-fight-coronavirus-idUSKBN20Z04U |archive-date=14 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Trump also said that \"As a result a large number of new clusters in the United States were seeded by travellers from Europe.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus: What you need to know about Trump's Europe travel ban |url=https://www.thelocal.dk/20200312/trump-imposes-travel-ban-from-europe-over-coronavirus-outbreak |work=The Local |date=12 March 2020}}</ref> Research on [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2|coronavirus genomes]] indicates the majority of COVID-19 cases in [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in New York (state)|New York]] came from European travelers, rather than directly from China or any other Asian country.<ref>{{cite news |title=Studies Show N.Y. Outbreak Originated in Europe|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/08/us/coronavirus-live-updates.html |work=The New York Times |date=April 8, 2020}}</ref> \n\nBy 9 March Czech Prime Minister [[Andrej Babi\u0161]] stated that \"European countries cannot ban the entry of Italian citizens within the Schengen area. The only possible way is to have the Italian prime minister call on his fellow citizens to refrain from traveling to other countries of the European Union.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.schengenvisainfo.com/news/czech-pm-italians-should-be-banned-from-travelling-due-to-coronavirus/ |title=Czech PM: Italians Should Be Banned From Travelling Due to Coronavirus |date=9 March 2020 |work=SchengenVisaInfo.com |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323171345/https://www.schengenvisainfo.com/news/czech-pm-italians-should-be-banned-from-travelling-due-to-coronavirus/ |archive-date=23 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nAfter Czech Republic, Slovakia, Poland and Denmark announced complete closure of their national borders, the [[European Commission]] President [[Ursula von der Leyen]] said by 12 March that \"Certain controls may be justified, but general travel bans are not seen as being the most effective by the World Health Organization. Moreover, they have a strong social and economic impact, they disrupt people\u2019s lives and business across the borders.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.ft.com/content/4e89ec5c-6565-11ea-b3f3-fe4680ea68b5 |title=Denmark, Poland and Czechs seal borders over coronavirus |date=12 March 2020 |agency=Financial Times |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314202823/https://www.ft.com/content/4e89ec5c-6565-11ea-b3f3-fe4680ea68b5 |archive-date=14 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> European Union leaders condemned the US decision to restrict travel from Europe to the United States. [[European Council]] President [[Charles Michel]] and Ursula von der Leyen said in a joint statement: \"The European Union disapproves of the fact that the US decision to impose a travel ban was taken unilaterally and without consultation.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://apnews.com/4552fd280d06cf83c63e4cc9b08fe5ce |title=EU condemns Trump travel ban from Europe as virus spreads |date=12 March 2020 |work=Associated Press (AP) |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200313140528/https://apnews.com/4552fd280d06cf83c63e4cc9b08fe5ce |archive-date=13 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Ursula von der Leyen admitted by 17 March that \"all of us who are not experts initially underestimated the coronavirus.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.euractiv.com/section/coronavirus/news/politicians-underestimated-virus-threat-von-der-leyen-admits/ |title=Politicians 'underestimated' virus threat, von der Leyen admits |date=18 March 2020 |work=Euractiv |access-date=21 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319152350/https://www.euractiv.com/section/coronavirus/news/politicians-underestimated-virus-threat-von-der-leyen-admits/ |archive-date=19 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nThe Italian government has criticised EU's lack of solidarity with Italy.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://foreignpolicy.com/2020/03/14/coronavirus-eu-abandoning-italy-china-aid/ |title=The EU Is Abandoning Italy in Its Hour of Need |date=14 March 2020 |work=Foreign Policy |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315112947/https://foreignpolicy.com/2020/03/14/coronavirus-eu-abandoning-italy-china-aid/ |archive-date=15 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/11/italy-criticises-eu-being-slow-help-coronavirus-epidemic |title=Italy criticises EU for being slow to help over coronavirus epidemic |date=11 March 2020 |work=The Guardian |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200313000621/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/11/italy-criticises-eu-being-slow-help-coronavirus-epidemic |archive-date=13 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.ft.com/content/d3bc25ea-652c-11ea-b3f3-fe4680ea68b5 |title=Italy wonders where Europe's solidarity is as coronavirus strains show |date=13 March 2020 |work=Financial Times |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315154437/https://www.ft.com/content/d3bc25ea-652c-11ea-b3f3-fe4680ea68b5 |archive-date=15 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://news.cgtn.com/news/2020-03-12/Italy-calls-for-extra-help-for-COVID-19-only-China-responded--ONp6w2rmvu/index.html |title=Italy criticizes EU for not responding its call for help, 'only China responded bilaterally' |date=12 March 2020 |work=CGTN |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200316024124/https://news.cgtn.com/news/2020-03-12/Italy-calls-for-extra-help-for-COVID-19-only-China-responded--ONp6w2rmvu/index.html |archive-date=16 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> ''Politico'' reported on 7 March that \"EU countries have so far refused Italy's plea for help fighting coronavirus, as national capitals worry that they may need to stockpile face masks and other medical gear to help their own citizens, officials and diplomats said.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.politico.eu/article/eu-aims-better-control-coronavirus-responses/ |title=Europe fails to help Italy in coronavirus fight |date=7 March 2020 |work=Politico |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317055659/https://www.politico.eu/article/eu-aims-better-control-coronavirus-responses/ |archive-date=17 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Maurizio Massari, Italy's ambassador to the EU, said that \"Only China responded bilaterally. Certainly, this is not a good sign of European solidarity.\"<ref name=\"politico-corona\" /> [[Serbia]]n President [[Aleksandar Vu\u010di\u0107]] said that \"European solidarity does not exist. That was a fairy tale.\"<ref name=\"politico-corona\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.politico.eu/article/coronavirus-china-winning-propaganda-war/ |title=China is winning the coronavirus propaganda war |date=18 March 2020 |work=Politico |access-date=21 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322203919/https://www.politico.eu/article/coronavirus-china-winning-propaganda-war/ |archive-date=22 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nThe planned [[NATO]] \u201c[[List of NATO exercises|Defender 2020]]\u201d military exercise in Germany, Poland, and the Baltic states,<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.spectator.co.uk/article/how-coronavirus-derailed-the-largest-nato-exercise-in-25-years |title=How coronavirus derailed the largest Nato exercise in 25 years |date=20 March 2020 |work=The Spectator |access-date=25 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200325102257/https://www.spectator.co.uk/article/how-coronavirus-derailed-the-largest-nato-exercise-in-25-years |archive-date=25 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> the largest NATO war manoeuvres since the end of the [[Cold War]], was to be held on a reduced scale because of the coronavirus pandemic.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-nato/nato-scales-down-exercises-due-to-coronavirus-idUSKBN21627V |title=NATO scales down exercises due to coronavirus |date=19 March 2020 |agency=Reuters |access-date=25 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200325102254/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-nato/nato-scales-down-exercises-due-to-coronavirus-idUSKBN21627V |archive-date=25 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> The [[Campaign for Nuclear Disarmament]]'s general secretary [[Kate Hudson (activist)|Kate Hudson]] critisiced the Defender 2020 exercise: \"In the current public-health crisis, it jeopardises the lives not only of the troops from the US and the many European countries participating but the inhabitants of the countries in which they are operating.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://morningstaronline.co.uk/article/b/nato-must-end-dangerous-and-irresponsible-military-exercise-on-russias-border-campaigners-say |title=Nato must end 'dangerous and irresponsible' military exercise on Russia's border, campaigners say |date=18 March 2020 |work=Morning Star |access-date=25 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320010441/https://morningstaronline.co.uk/article/b/nato-must-end-dangerous-and-irresponsible-military-exercise-on-russias-border-campaigners-say |archive-date=20 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[PREPARE]] (EU PREPARE project)\n* [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{Notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|refs=\n<ref name=\"OKOpress_Szumowski_EU_claims\">{{cite news | last1= Pa\u0144kowska | first1= Maria | language =pl | title= Szumowski krytykuje UE: 'Nie ma tej europejskiej solidarno\u015bci'. To wielopi\u0119trowy fa\u0142sz |trans-title = Szumowski criticise the EU: 'There is no European solidarity'. Which is false at many levels<!-- trans-title is the English translation --> | date= 2020-03-26 |newspaper= [[OKO.press]] | url= https://oko.press/szumowski-krytykuje-ue-nie-ma-tej-europejskiej-solidarnosci-to-wielopietrowy-falsz/ |quote= Bo jak by\u015bmy czekali na inne kraje, na Europ\u0119, na \u015bwiat, to by\u015bmy si\u0119 obudzili bez \u015brodk\u00f3w, a dooko\u0142a wszyscy by te \u015brodki sobie zakupili ... \u017beby by\u0142a jasno\u015b\u0107, to nie jest tak, \u017ce my ten sprz\u0119t mamy w Europie, \u017ce s\u0105 jego nieograniczone ilo\u015bci. ... Bo niestety tutaj centralne zakupy zawiod\u0142y, nie ma tej europejskiej solidarno\u015bci.  |accessdate=2020-03-26 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20200326225848/https://oko.press/szumowski-krytykuje-ue-nie-ma-tej-europejskiej-solidarnosci-to-wielopietrowy-falsz/ |archivedate= 2020-03-26 |url-status=live <!-- live|dead|unfit|usurped --> |url-access = <!-- (subscription/registration/limited) default=free -->}}</ref>\n}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://corona.arrangy.com Worldwide Coronavirus Map, confirmed Cases] \u2013 Map the route paths of coronavirus confirmed cases.\n* [https://systems.jhu.edu/research/public-health/ncov/ ncov \u2013 CSSE] \u2013 Map of the expansion of the virus in Europe and in the world\n{{COVID-19}}\n\n[[Category:2020 in Europe|coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:Health disasters in Europe]]\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by continent|Europe]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Europe| ]]\n", "name_user": "Nuzaliwaj", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eStatistics by country", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_Europe"}
{"title_page": "Trolls (film)", "text_new": "{{distinguish|Troll (film)}}\n{{short description|2016 US computer animated film directed by Mike Mitchell}}\n{{Use American English|date = October 2016}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Trolls\n| image          = Trolls (film) logo.png\n| alt            = \n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Mike Mitchell (director)|Mike Mitchell]]\n| producer       = [[Gina Shay]]<ref name=PRNSlate2016 />\n| screenplay     = {{ubl|[[Jonathan Aibel and Glenn Berger|Jonathan Aibel]]|[[Jonathan Aibel and Glenn Berger|Glenn Berger]]}}\n| story          = Erica Rivinoja<ref name=PRNSlate2016 />\n| based on       = {{based on|The [[Troll doll|Good Luck Trolls]]|[[Thomas Dam]]}}\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Anna Kendrick]]\n* [[Justin Timberlake]]\n* [[Zooey Deschanel]]\n* [[Russell Brand]]\n* [[James Corden]]\n* [[Gwen Stefani]]\n}}<!--PER poster billing block-->\n| music          = [[Christophe Beck]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Christophe Beck to Score DreamWorks Animation's \u2018Trolls\u2019|url=http://filmmusicreporter.com/2015/12/07/christophe-beck-to-score-dreamworks-animations-trolls/|publisher=Film Music Reporter|accessdate=December 9, 2015}}</ref>\n| cinematography = [[Yong Duk Jhun]]\n| editing        = [[Nick Fletcher]]\n| studio         = [[DreamWorks Animation]]<ref name=THRReview/>\n| distributor    = [[20th Century Fox]]\n| released       = {{Film date|2016|10|08|[[BFI London Film Festival]]|2016|11|04|United States}}\n| runtime        = 93 minutes<ref name=THRReview />\n| country        = United States<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allmovie.com/movie/trolls-v571273|title=Trolls (2016)|work=[[AllMovie]]|accessdate=June 4, 2017}}</ref>\n| language       = English\n| budget         = $125&nbsp;million<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/envelope/cotown/la-fi-ct-movie-projector-20161031-story.html|title='Doctor Strange' is expected to draw a massive audience for Disney's Marvel Studios|author=Ryan Faughnder|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|date=November 1, 2016|accessdate=November 2, 2016}}</ref>\n| gross          = $346.9&nbsp;million<ref name=\"BOM\">{{cite web |url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=trolls.htm |title=Trolls (2016) |website=Box Office Mojo |accessdate=June 8, 2017}}</ref>\n}}\n'''''Trolls''''' is a 2016 American [[computer animation|computer-animated]] [[Musical film|musical]]<ref name=\"VarietyReview\">{{cite news|last1=Gleiberman|first1=Owen|title=Film Review: \u2018Trolls\u2019|url=https://variety.com/2016/film/reviews/trolls-review-justin-timberlake-anna-kendrick-1201880434/|accessdate=December 20, 2016|work=Variety|date=October 8, 2016}}</ref> [[comedy film]]<ref>[https://festivalreviews.org/2016/11/04/film-review-trolls-usa-2016/ Film Review: TROLLS (USA 2016) ***]</ref> based on the [[Troll doll]]s created by [[Thomas Dam]]. [[Mike Mitchell (director)|Mike Mitchell]] directed the film, with [[Jonathan Aibel and Glenn Berger]] serving as the writers. ''Trolls'' is based on a story by Erica Rivinoja. The film features the voices of [[Anna Kendrick]], [[Justin Timberlake]], [[Christopher Mintz-Plasse]], [[Zooey Deschanel]], [[Christine Baranski]], [[Russell Brand]], [[James Corden]], [[Jeffrey Tambor]], [[Ron Funches]], [[Icona Pop|Caroline Hjelt]], [[Icona Pop|Aino Jawo]], [[Kunal Nayyar]], [[John Cleese]] and [[Gwen Stefani]]. The film follows two trolls who go on a quest, to save their village from destruction by the Bergens, creatures who eat Trolls to be happy.\n\nThe 33rd animated feature film produced by [[DreamWorks Animation]], the film premiered on October 8, 2016, at the [[BFI London Film Festival]]<ref name=THRReview /><ref>{{cite web|title=BFI London Film Festival \u2013 Trolls|url=https://whatson.bfi.org.uk/lff/Online/default.asp?BOparam::WScontent::loadArticle::permalink=trolls|publisher=British Film Institute|accessdate=October 9, 2016}}</ref> and was theatrically released in the United States on November 4, 2016, by [[20th Century Fox]].<ref name=DeadlineTimberlake>{{cite web|last1=Lieberman|first1=David|title=Justin Timberlake To Add His Voice To DreamWorks Animation's \u2018Trolls\u2019|url=https://deadline.com/2015/09/justin-timberlake-joins-trolls-dreamworks-animation-1201527740/|website=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=September 15, 2015|date=September 15, 2015}}</ref> The film received mostly positive reviews from critics, grossed $346&nbsp;million worldwide against its $125&nbsp;million budget and received an [[Academy Awards|Academy Award]] nomination for [[Academy Award for Best Original Song|Best Original Song]] for \"[[Can't Stop the Feeling!]]\". A sequel, ''[[Trolls World Tour]]'', was released on April 10, 2020.\n\n==Plot==   \n<!-- Please see WP:FILMPLOT before editing. Per key guideline, the plot summary should be within the desired length of 400-700 words. -->\nThe Trolls are small, colorful creatures who live in an almost perpetual state of happiness, singing, dancing, hugging, and having fun all day. However, they are discovered by the ''Bergens'', large, ugly, miserable creatures who can only feel happy by consuming a Troll. The Bergens imprison the trolls and eat them every year on a special occasion, called \"Trollstice\". The Trolls, led by their king, King Peppy, with his infant daughter, Princess Poppy, escape through tunnels on the day of Trollstice when Prince Gristle Jr. was going to eat his first Troll. Enraged, Gristle Jr.\u2019s father King Gristle Sr. banishes his Chef, who was in charge of preparing for Trollstice. Chef promises to leave and find the Trolls herself.\n\nTwenty years later, the now-adult Poppy throws a big party to celebrate the Trolls' escape, despite the warnings of the over-cautious and egotistical gray troll, Branch, that loud parties will attract the Bergens. A \"Zen\" troll named Creek arrives and tells Branch to start being happy instead of being grumpy; Branch refuses. At the party, Branch's warnings come true when Chef sees the fireworks and kidnaps Poppy's friends Guy Diamond, Biggie with Mr. Dinkles, Fuzzbert, Smidge, Satin with Chenille, DJ Suki, and Cooper, along with Creek, despite Poppy trying to rescue him and King Peppy. Chef takes the kidnapped Trolls back to Bergen Town while secretly plotting to overthrow its monarchy as revenge for her exile.\n\nMeanwhile, Poppy goes on a rescue mission alone, as no other troll is willing to venture towards Bergen Town. But later on, when Poppy gets into trouble, she is saved by Branch who thinks she will not make it if she goes alone. Once inside the Bergen king's castle, Poppy and Branch witness the now-King Gristle Jr. seemingly eat Creek, but Poppy remains hopeful that Creek survived. Poppy and Branch find the rest of the captured Trolls being guarded by a scullery maid named Bridget. Poppy discovers that Bridget is secretly in love with King Gristle Jr. and offers to help her get a date with the king while trying to confirm if Creek is alive.\n\nWhile setting Bridget up for the date with a musical number, Branch refuses to sing and triggers an argument with Poppy, revealing that, as a child, his grandmother was captured and got eaten while trying to save him, because his singing compromised his location to Chef. Branch's complete guilt over his grandmother's death caused his color to turn from blue to gray.\n\nAfter Poppy comforts him with a hug, Branch decides to help Bridget and the trolls, though he still refuses to sing. Bridget, disguised under the name of \"Lady Glittersparkles\" gets her date with Gristle Jr. at a [[roller rink]] and [[amusement arcade|arcade restaurant]] and Gristle Jr. asks her to be his \"plus one\" at Trollstice. Poppy notices Creek being held captive inside the jewel adorning the king's mantle.\n\nHaving helped Bridget, the Trolls attempt to rescue Creek from Gristle's room and steal his jewel but discover that it is empty. The Trolls are then captured by Chef, and Poppy gets shocked to discover that Creek sold them out to the Bergens to spare himself from being eaten. Creek lures out every troll from Troll Village (via Poppy's cowbell) and they are captured by Chef and the other Bergen cooks. With all the Trolls captured, thrown into a pot and soon to be eaten, a heartbroken Poppy falls into despair and loses hope as she and all the other Trolls turn gray.\n\nBranch tries to sing \"[[True Colors (Cyndi Lauper song)|True Colors]]\" for Poppy to cheer her up, confessing his love for her. Poppy, after regaining her colors, returns his feelings, and they restore all the trolls' colors, including Branch's. Bridget saves the trolls, willing to sacrifice herself. Poppy can't bring herself to abandon Bridget and, with Branch and her friends, shows Gristle Jr. and the Bergens that Bridget is Lady Glittersparkles and that it is not necessary to eat Trolls to be happy, and they too, can find happiness within themselves.\n\nThe vengeful Chef refuses to accept the peace and tries to kill the Trolls, but is knocked into a serving cart that is sent rolling out of Bergen Town. Chef is set on fire with Creek, who was still in her pouch. Both species celebrate, bringing new life to the town. Poppy is then declared queen of the Trolls, and Poppy and Branch share a friendly hug.\n\nIn a [[Post-credits scene|mid-credits scene]], Chef and Creek's cart stops rolling. Chef prepares to eat Creek herself, but they soon find out they are on top of a monster, who opens his mouth and eats them both.\n\n==Cast==\n{{multiple image\n|direction = horizontal\n|image1    = Anna Kendrick Cannes 2016.jpg\n|width1    = 149\n|alt1      = Anna Kendrick\n|image2    = Justin Timberlake Cannes 2016.jpg\n|width2    = 130\n|alt2      = Justin Timberlake\n|footer    = Anna Kendrick and Justin Timberlake at the film's preview at the [[2016 Cannes Film Festival]]<ref>{{cite news|last1=Lawson|first1=Richard|last2=Miller|first2=Julie|title=What Happened When Justin Timberlake, Anna Kendrick, and Trolls Came to Cannes|url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2016/05/anna-kendrick-justin-timberlake-trolls-cannes|accessdate=July 24, 2016|work=Vanity Fair|date=May 12, 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n* [[Anna Kendrick]] as Poppy, the princess, and later queen, of the Trolls.   <ref name=DeadlineTimberlake /><ref name=\"comingsoon1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.comingsoon.net/news/movienews.php?id=119556 |title=Anna Kendrick to Voice DreamWorks Animation's Trolls |publisher=ComingSoon.net |accessdate=June 17, 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"twitter1\">{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/AnnaKendrick47/status/684782188907237376 |title=Hair we go! Meet Poppy! #DreamWorksTrolls #HairGoals #NewYearNewMe |publisher=Twitter |first1=Anna |last1=Kendrick| date=January 6, 2016 |accessdate=January 6, 2016}}</ref>\n** Iris Dohrn as Baby Poppy\n* [[Justin Timberlake]] as Branch, an over-cautious  pessimist Troll survivalist, who has a secret crush on Poppy. <ref name=DeadlineTimberlake /><ref name=\"twitter2\">{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/jtimberlake/status/684781983826710528 |title=Hair we go...I'm officially a #Troll.  #TrollsMovie #MeetBranch #HairPuns #ItsJustTheBeginning |publisher=Twitter |last1=Timberlake |first1=Justin |date=January 6, 2016 |accessdate=January 6, 2016}}</ref>\n** Liam Henry as Young Branch\n*[[Christopher Mintz-Plasse]] as King Gristle Jr., the prince/king of the Bergens.<ref name=\"thr-cast\" />\n*[[Zooey Deschanel]] as Bridget, a kind-hearted Bergen who works as a [[scullery maid]] to the Bergen Chef. She also had a secret crush on Gristle Jr.<ref name=\"thr-cast\" />\n*[[Christine Baranski]] as the evil and power-hungry royal chef of the Bergens.<ref name=\"thr-cast\" />\n*[[Russell Brand]] as Creek, a Troll with a \"positive\" personality and \"zen\"-like wisdom. He later turned out to be a coward, a faker and a traitor, when he told the Bergens where the other Trolls were, just so he can save himself.<ref name=\"thr-cast\" /><ref name=\"twitter6\">{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/rustyrockets/status/684781697511108608 |title=Hair we go! Meet Creek! #DreamWorksTrolls #LetYourHairUp |publisher=Twitter |first=Russel |last1=Brand |date=January 6, 2016 |accessdate=January 6, 2016}}</ref>\n* [[James Corden]] as Biggie, a large Troll.<ref name=thr-cast/><ref name=\"twitter5\">{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/JKCorden/status/684781501414690816 |title=Hair we go! Meet Biggie! #DreamWorksTrolls #TheySeeMeTrollin |publisher=Twitter |last1=Corden |first1=James |date=January 6, 2016 |accessdate=January 6, 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Jeffrey Tambor]] as King Peppy, the king of the Trolls who once led his Trolls to freedom from the Bergens and Poppy's father.<ref name=thr-cast/>\n* [[John Cleese]] as King Gristle Sr., the ruler of the Bergens at the start of the film.<ref name=\"thr-cast\" />\n* [[Gwen Stefani]] as DJ Suki, the Trolls' resident DJ Troll who uses DJ equipment made of insects.<ref name=thr-cast>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/zooey-deschanel-jeffrey-tambor-join-884064|title=Zooey Deschanel, Jeffrey Tambor Join DreamWorks Animation's 'Trolls'|last=Vlessing|first=Etan|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=April 14, 2016|accessdate=April 19, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"twitter4\">{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/gwenstefani/status/684799797291692032 |title=Hair we go! Meet DJ Suki! #DreamWorksTrolls #RockinTroll |publisher=Twitter |last1=Stefani |first1=Gwen |date=January 6, 2016 |accessdate=January 6, 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Ron Funches]] as Cooper, a giraffe-like Troll.<ref name=thr-cast/><ref name=\"twitter8\">{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/RonFunches/status/684785415228788737 |title=Remember Trolls?! They're back! In Ron form.  #DreamWorksTrolls |publisher=Twitter |last1=Funches |first1=Ronald |date=January 6, 2016 |accessdate=January 6, 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Icona Pop|Caroline Hjelt]] as Chenille, a Troll who alongside her twin sister Satin are the most fashion forward<ref name=\"twitter7\"/>\n* [[Icona Pop|Aino Jawo]] as Satin, a Troll who alongside her twin sister Chenille are the most fashion forward.<ref name=thr-cast/><ref name=\"twitter7\">{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/iconapop/status/684781559078084608 |title=Hair we go! Meet the Fashionistas! #DreamWorksTrolls #TwiceAsNice |publisher=Twitter |author=Icona Pop |date=January 6, 2016 |accessdate=January 6, 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Kunal Nayyar]] as Guy Diamond, a gray glittery Troll who is always naked.<ref name=thr-cast/><ref name=\"twitter9\">{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/kunalnayyar/status/684781765026656257 |title=Hair we go! Meet Guy Diamond! #DreamWorksTrolls #ShineBrightLikeGuyDiamond |publisher=Twitter |last1=Nayyar |first1=Kunal |date=January 6, 2016 |accessdate=January 6, 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Quvenzhan\u00e9 Wallis]] as Harper, a Troll artist with [[heterochromia]] who paints with her hair.<ref name=thr-cast/>\n* [[GloZell]] as Grandma Rosiepuff, an elderly Troll and Branch's late grandmother.<ref name=official>{{cite web|url=http://www.dreamworks.com/trolls/|title=Trolls Official Website|work=[[DreamWorks Animation|DreamWorks]]|accessdate=April 19, 2016}}</ref> [[Dami Im]] voices the character in the Australian version.{{cn|date=April 2020}} [[Susanna Reid]] voices the character in the UK version.<ref name=\"ok.co.uk\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ok.co.uk/tv/daytime/good-morning-britains-susanna-reid-14736809 |title=Good Morning Britain's Susanna Reid lands debut film role in Trolls}}</ref>\n* Meg DeAngelis as Moxie Dewdrop, a dancing Troll.<ref name=official/> [[Connie Glynn]] voices the character in the UK version.\n* [[Ricky Dillon]] as Aspen Heitz, a Troll skitterboarder.<ref name=official/> [[Greg James]] voices the character in the UK version.<ref name=\"ok.co.uk\"/>\n* Kandee Johnson as Mandy Sparkledust, a Troll who designs and repairs all the treasures of Troll Town.<ref name=official/> [[Abbey Clancy]] voices the character in the UK version.<ref name=\"ok.co.uk\"/>\n* [[Walt Dohrn]] as :<ref name=thr-cast/>\n** Smidge, a small female troll with a masculine voice.\n** Mr. Dinkles, Biggie's pet worm.\n** Fuzzbert, a hair troll with two legs.\n** Cloud Guy, an anthropomorphic cloud.\n* [[Mike Mitchell (director)|Mike Mitchell]] as Darius / Vinny / Captain Starfunkle / Spider / Wedgie Bergen #1 / Chad / Card\n* [[Grace Helbig]] as Cookie Sugarloaf, one of the trolls. [[Carrie Hope Fletcher]] voices the character in the UK version.<ref name=\"uk version\">{{cite web|url=https://teneightymagazine.com/2016/09/13/carrie-hope-fletcher-and-noodlerella-join-the-cast-of-trolls/|title=Carrie Hope Fletcher and Noodlerella Join the Cast of Trolls|journal=TenEighty|first=Kiersten|last=Nordin|date=13 September 2016|accessdate=10 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Fletcher|first1=Carrie|title=Voicing A Troll|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nlV0HFohupo|via=YouTube|publisher=Carrie Hope Fletcher|accessdate=December 3, 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Curtis Stone]] as Todd, a royal guard that works for the Bergen Royal Family.\n* [[Rhys Darby]] as Bibbly, a Bergen shopkeeper of the Bib Store.\n\n==Production==\n[[File:Mike Mitchell & Walt Dohrn, Trolls, 2016 San Diego Comic-Con International.jpg|thumb|right|Director [[Mike Mitchell (director)|Mike Mitchell]] and co-director [[Walt Dohrn]] presented footage from the film at the 2016 [[San Diego Comic-Con International]]]]\nDreamWorks announced plans for a film based on the Troll toyline as early as 2010. This version was to be written by Adam Wilson and Melanie Wilson LaBracio.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Lesnick|first1=Silas|title=DreamWorks Animation Plans Good Luck Trolls Film|url=https://www.comingsoon.net/movies/news/67234-dreamworks-animation-plans-good-luck-trolls-film|website=Coming Soon.net|accessdate=November 5, 2016}}</ref> By 2012, [[Chlo\u00eb Grace Moretz]] had already been cast in the female lead role and [[Jason Schwartzman]] was reported to have been offered the male lead.<ref name=DeadlineSchwartzman>{{cite magazine|last=Fleming|first=Mike|title=Jason Schwartzman In \u2018Trolls\u2019 Mode?|url=https://www.deadline.com/2012/06/jason-schwartzman-in-trolls-mode/|accessdate=June 25, 2012|magazine=Deadline Hollywood|date=June 20, 2012}}</ref> In September 2012, [[20th Century Fox]] and [[DreamWorks Animation]] announced that the film with the working title ''Trolls'' would be released on June 5, 2015, with [[Anand Tucker]] set to direct the film, written by [[Wallace Wolodarsky]] and [[Maya Forbes]].<ref name=PRNSlate2016>{{cite press release|author1=DreamWorks Animation|title=New Distributor Twentieth Century Fox Unveils DreamWorks Animation's Release Slate Through 2016|url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/new-distributor-twentieth-century-fox-unveils-dreamworks-animations-release-slate-through-2016-169123176.html|agency=PR Newswire|accessdate=December 13, 2014|date=September 9, 2012}}</ref>\n\nBy April 2013, DreamWorks Animation had acquired the intellectual property for the [[Troll doll|Trolls franchise]] from the Dam Family and Dam Things. Having \"big plans for the franchise,\" DreamWorks Animation became the exclusive worldwide licensor of the merchandise rights, except for Scandinavia, where Dam Things remains the licensor.<ref>{{cite news|title=DreamWorks Animation Acquires IP For Trolls With Plans To Take Iconic Dolls' Brand (And Hair) To New Heights|url=http://ir.dreamworksanimation.com/releasedetail.cfm?ReleaseID=756128|accessdate=April 13, 2013|newspaper=DreamWorks Animation|date=April 11, 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130506030237/http://ir.dreamworksanimation.com/releasedetail.cfm?ReleaseID=756128|archivedate=May 6, 2013}}</ref> In May 2013, the film was pushed back for a year to November 4, 2016.<ref name=Collider2016>{{cite news|last=Chitwood|first=Adam|title=DreamWorks Animation Moves B.O.O. Release Up to June 5, 2015 and TROLLS to November 4, 2016; Fox Dates ANUBIS and FERDINAND|url=https://collider.com/boo-release-date-trolls-release-date-dreamworks-animation/|accessdate=May 16, 2013|newspaper=Collider.com|date=May 16, 2013}}</ref> The same month, DreamWorks Animation announced that [[Mike Mitchell (director)|Mike Mitchell]] and Erica Rivinoja has been hired as a director and screenplay writer to \"reimagine\" the film as a musical comedy, which would present the origin of the Trolls' colorful hair.<ref name=DWAMitchell>{{cite news|title=Acclaimed Comedy Director Mike Mitchell And Emmy Award Winning Writer Erica Rivinoja Bring DreamWorks' Trolls to the Big Screen|url=http://ir.dreamworksanimation.com/releasedetail.cfm?ReleaseID=767658|accessdate=May 31, 2013|newspaper=DreamWorks Animation|date=May 28, 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130629021843/http://ir.dreamworksanimation.com/releasedetail.cfm?ReleaseID=767658|archivedate=June 29, 2013}}</ref> On June 16, 2014, [[Anna Kendrick]] joined the cast to voice Poppy, a princess.<ref name=\"comingsoon1\" /> On September 15, 2015, ''[[Deadline Hollywood]]'' reported that [[Justin Timberlake]] would voice a character named Branch.<ref name=DeadlineTimberlake /> Timberlake previously worked with DreamWorks Animation as the voice of Arthur \"Artie\" Pendragon in ''[[Shrek the Third]]'' in 2007. The full cast announced their respective roles via announcements on Twitter on January 6, 2016.<ref name=\"bcdb1\">{{cite web |url=http://blog.bcdb.com/dreamworks-announces-a-cast-of-trolls-9414/ |title=DreamWorks Announces a Cast of Trolls |publisher=BCDB Blog |date=January 6, 2016 |accessdate=January 6, 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20160224061131/http://blog.bcdb.com/dreamworks-announces-a-cast-of-trolls-9414/ |archivedate=February 24, 2016  }}</ref>\n\n==Music==\n{{main|Trolls (soundtrack)}}\nJustin Timberlake served as an executive producer for the film's music and released the original song \"[[Can't Stop the Feeling!]]\" in conjunction with \"[[Hello Darkness]]\" on May 6, 2016.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7357815/justin-timberlake-cant-stop-the-feeling-new-song | title=Justin Timberlake Delivers Delightful Single 'Can't Stop The Feeling': Watch | work=Billboard | date=May 6, 2016 | accessdate=May 6, 2016 | author=Platon, Adelle}}</ref> The song reached No. 1 in the official charts of 17 countries, including the [[Billboard Hot 100|United States]] and [[Canadian Hot 100|Canada]]. In addition to Timberlake, the rest of the cast contributed to the film's soundtrack, which also features guest appearances from [[Earth, Wind & Fire]] and [[Ariana Grande]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/7357909/justin-timberlake-talks-trolls-soundtrack-new-music | title=Justin Timberlake Talks 'Trolls' Soundtrack and New Music | work=Billboard | date=May 6, 2016 | accessdate=May 6, 2016 | author=Kaufman, Gil}}</ref> The soundtrack album was certified [[Music recording sales certification|Platinum]] by the [[Recording Industry Association of America]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/?tab_active=default-award&se=TROLLS+%28ORIGINAL+MOTION+PICTURE+SOUNDTRACK%29#search_section |title= American certifications \u2013 Trolls |accessdate=January 5, 2017 |work=[[Recording Industry Association of America]]}}</ref> and the [[Australian Recording Industry Association]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ariacharts.com.au/charts/albums-chart |title=Aria Albums Chart |date=January 4, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Release==\nThe film's opening premiere opened at the [[BFI London Film Festival]] Opening Celebration on October 8, 2016 as a special BFI presentation, and was theatrically released on November 4, 2016, in the United States by [[20th Century Fox]].\n\nThe studio spent an estimated $105 million promoting the film.<ref name=DeadlineProfit/>\n\n===Home media===\n''Trolls'' was released on Digital HD on January 24, 2017, and on DVD and [[Blu-ray]] on February 7, 2017.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Milligan|first1=Mercedes|title=DWA's \u2018Trolls\u2019 Brings the Happy Home on Disc & Digital|url=http://www.animationmagazine.net/home-entertainment/dwas-trolls-brings-the-happy-home-on-disc-digital/|accessdate=January 14, 2017|work=Animation Magazine|date=January 11, 2017}}</ref> The film topped the home video sales chart for two consecutive weeks.<ref>[https://variety.com/2017/digital/news/trolls-tops-disc-sales-charts-1201989743/ \u2018Trolls\u2019 Tops Disc Sales Charts] Variety. Retrieved February 23, 2017</ref><ref>[https://variety.com/2017/digital/news/trolls-trumps-arrival-to-remain-no-1-on-disc-sales-charts-1201994191/ \u2018Trolls\u2019 Trumps \u2018Arrival\u2019 to Remain No. 1 on Disc Sales Charts] Variety. Retrieved February 23, 2017</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n===Box office===\n''Trolls'' grossed $153.7&nbsp;million in the US and Canada and $193.2&nbsp;million in other countries for a worldwide total of $346.8&nbsp;million, against a budget of $125&nbsp;million.<ref name=BOM /> ''[[Deadline Hollywood]]'' calculated the film made a net profit of $19&nbsp;million, when factoring together all expenses and revenues.<ref name=DeadlineProfit>{{cite web|url= https://deadline.com/2020/04/trolls-world-tour-vod-box-office-movie-profits-universal-coronavirus-1202903913/ |title= Will \u2018Trolls World Tour\u2019 Profit Off Universal\u2019s Experimental VOD (& Drive-In Theater) Model?|first=Anthony|last=D'Alessandro|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 10, 2019|accessdate=April 10, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn the United States and Canada, ''Trolls'' was released alongside the releases of ''[[Doctor Strange (2016 film)|Doctor Strange]]'' and ''[[Hacksaw Ridge]]'', and was projected to gross $35\u201340&nbsp;million from 4,060 theaters in its opening weekend.<ref name=\"preview\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2016/11/doctor-strange-hacksaw-ridge-mel-gibson-trolls-1201846210/ |title=\u2018Doctor Strange\u2019 To Give Booster Shot To Sleepy Fall Box Office |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]}}</ref> On its first day, the film grossed $12.3&nbsp;million (including $900,000 made from Thursday night previews). It went on to open to $46.5&nbsp;million, finishing second at the box office behind ''Doctor Strange''.<ref name=\"DeadlineWknd1\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2016/11/doctor-strange-trolls-hacksaw-ridge-weekend-box-office-1201848529/|title=\u2018Doctor Strange\u2019 Resuscitates Fall Box Office With $81M To $83M+ Opening \u2013 Saturday AM Update|last=D'Alessandro|first=Anthony|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|accessdate=November 6, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Critical response===\nOn [[review aggregator]] website [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the film holds an approval rating of 76% based on 161 reviews, with an average rating of 6.28/10. The site's critical consensus reads: \"''Trolls'' brings its instantly recognizable characters to the big screen in a colorful adventure that, while geared toward the younger set, isn't without rewards for parents.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/trolls/|title=Trolls (2016)|work=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|publisher=[[Fandango Media]]|accessdate=May 23, 2019}}</ref> On [[Metacritic]], which assigns a normalized rating, the film has a score of 55 out of 100, based on 32 critics, indicating \"mixed or average reviews\".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/movie/trolls |title=Trolls Reviews |website=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=November 10, 2016}}</ref> Audiences polled by [[CinemaScore]] gave the film an average grade of \"A\" on an A+ to F scale, while [[PostTrak]] reported filmgoers gave it an 80% overall positive score.<ref name=\"DeadlineWknd1\"/>\n\nLindsey Bahr of [[Associated Press]] gave the film a positive review and said, \"Ultimately, the 'get happy' moral of the story, while trite compared to something like ''[[Inside Out (2015 film)|Inside Out]]'', is sufficiently sweet enough for its audience. Did you expect more from a piece of candy?\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.torontosun.com/2016/11/02/review-trolls-is-big-hearted-sensory-overload|title=Review: 'Trolls' is big-hearted sensory overload|first1=Lindsey|last1=Bahr|first2=The Associated|last2=Press}}</ref> Bill Zwecker of ''[[Chicago Sun-Times]]'' gave the film three-and-a-half stars out of four and said, \"You simply will walk out \u2013 or perhaps dance out \u2013 of the theater feeling very happy yourself.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://chicago.suntimes.com/entertainment/trolls-review/|title=Delightful 'Trolls' achieves maximum smiles per hour}}</ref> Andy Webster of ''[[The New York Times]]'' said, \"Exuberant, busy and sometimes funny, DreamWorks Animation's ''Trolls'' is determined to amuse.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/11/04/movies/trolls-review.html|title=Review: The \u2018Trolls\u2019 Embark on a High-Haired Rescue Mission|date=November 3, 2016|work=The New York Times}}</ref>\n\nMichael Rechtshaffen, writing for ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'', called the film \"an admittedly vibrant-looking but awfully recognizable animated musical comedy concoction.\"<ref name=\"THRReview\">{{cite news|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/trolls-film-review-936514|title='Trolls': Film Review|author=Rechtshaffen|first=Michael|date=October 8, 2016|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|accessdate=November 11, 2019}}</ref> [[Alonso Duralde]] of [[TheWrap]] said the film \"combines the barely-there characterization and irritating cutesiness of ''[[The Smurfs (film)|The Smurfs]]'' with the hideous character design and awful pop covers of ''[[Strange Magic (film)|Strange Magic]]''.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thewrap.com/trolls-review-justin-timberlake/|title=\u2018Trolls\u2019 London Review: Justin Timberlake and Anna Kendrick Are Floppin\u2019 to Oldies|author=[[Alonso Duralde]]|work=[[TheWrap]]|date=October 8, 2016|accessdate=October 8, 2016}}</ref> Betsy Bozdech of [[Common Sense Media]] gave the movie 4 stars. She said, \"Make no mistake: Kids are going to love this movie. Trolls is cute, it's colorful, it has tons of catchy songs, and the messages are positive and easy to understand (happiness is inside everyone, if you know where/how to find it, and you shouldn't have to change who you are to get someone to like you).\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.commonsensemedia.org/movie-reviews/trolls |title=Trolls Movie Review|first=Betsy|last=Bozdech|publisher=Common Sense Media|accessdate=August 27, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Accolades===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:small\"\n|- style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n! colspan=\"6\" style=\"background: LightSteelBlue;\" | List of awards and nominations\n|- style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n! Award\n! Date of ceremony\n! Category\n! Recipient(s)\n! Result\n! class=\"unsortable\"| {{nowrap|{{Abbr|Ref(s)|References}}}}\n|-\n| [[Academy Awards]]\n| [[89th Academy Awards|February 26, 2017]]\n| [[Academy Award for Best Original Song|Best Original Song]]\n| \"[[Can't Stop the Feeling!]]\" \u2013 [[Max Martin]], [[Shellback (record producer)|Shellback]] and [[Justin Timberlake]]\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"Oscars2017\">{{cite news |url=http://edit.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/oscar-nominations-2017-complete-list-nominees-960044 |title=Oscars: 'La La Land' Ties Record With 14 Nominations |first=Kimberly |last=Nordyke |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=January 24, 2017 |accessdate=January 24, 2017  }}{{dead link|date=November 2018|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref><br /><ref name=\"OscarsVar\">{{cite news|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/2017-oscar-nominations-academy-awards-nominees-1201968107/ |title=Oscar Nominations: Complete List |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=January 24, 2017 |accessdate=January 24, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[American Music Award]]s\n| [[American Music Awards of 2017|November 19, 2017]]\n| Top Soundtrack\n| ''[[Trolls (soundtrack)|Trolls: Original Motion Picture Soundtrack]]''\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"