t-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2017/tv/news/nickelodeon-kids-choice-awards-nominations-2017-full-list-1201975603/|title=Justin Timberlake and Kevin Hart Lead Nickelodeon's Kids\u2019 Choice Awards Nominations|work=Variety|date= February 24, 2017 |accessdate= February 24, 2017 }}</ref>\n|-\n| Favorite Voice From an Animated Movie\n| rowspan=\"2\" | Justin Timberlake and [[Anna Kendrick]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Favorite Frenemies\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Favorite Soundtrack\n| ''Trolls: Original Motion Picture Soundtrack''\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[Satellite Awards]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[21st Satellite Awards|February 19, 2017]]\n| [[Satellite Award for Best Animated or Mixed Media Feature|Best Animated or Mixed Media Feature]]\n| ''Trolls''\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/2016-satellite-awards-nominees-listed-includes-moonlight-la-la-land-950935|title=Satellite Awards Nominees Revealed|last=Kilday|first=Gregg|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=November 29, 2016|accessdate=November 29, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Satellite Award for Best Original Song|Best Original Song]]\n| \"Can't Stop the Feeling!\" \u2013 Max Martin, Shellback and Justin Timberlake\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Saturn Awards]]\n| [[43rd Saturn Awards|June 28, 2017]]\n| [[Saturn Award for Best Animated Film|Best Animated Film]]\n| rowspan=\"3\" | ''Trolls''\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"SaturnAwards\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/awards/saturn-awards-nominations-2017-rogue-one-walking-dead-1202000833/ |title=Saturn Awards Nominations 2017: 'Rogue One,' 'Walking Dead' Lead |last=McNary |first=Dave |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=March 2, 2017 |accessdate=March 3, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[St. Louis Gateway Film Critics Association]]\n| [[St. Louis Gateway Film Critics Association Awards 2016|December 18, 2016]]\n| Best Soundtrack\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.stlfilmcritics.org/awards |title=2016 StLFCA Annual Award Nominations |publisher=[[St. Louis Gateway Film Critics Association]] |date=December 12, 2016 |accessdate=December 12, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[Teen Choice Awards]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[2016 Teen Choice Awards|July 31, 2016]]\n| Choice AnTEENcipated Movie\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"TeenChoice\">{{cite web |url=http://www.eonline.com/news/767635/teen-choice-awards-2016-nominations-announced-see-the-first-wave-of-potential-winners |title=Teen Choice Awards 2016 Nominations Announced: See the \"First Wave\" of Potential Winners |last=Vulpo |first=Mike |publisher=[[E!]] |date=May 24, 2016 |accessdate=May 25, 2016 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6hm3YMtx8?url=http://www.eonline.com/news/767635/teen-choice-awards-2016-nominations-announced-see-the-first-wave-of-potential-winners |archivedate=May 25, 2016 |url-status=live  }}</ref>\n|-\n| Choice Music: Song from a Movie or TV Show\n| \"Can't Stop the Feeling!\" by Justin Timberlake\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[World Soundtrack Academy|World Soundtrack Awards]]\n| October 18, 2017\n| [[World Soundtrack Award for Best Original Song Written Directly for a Film|Best Original Song written directly for a Film]]\n| \"Can't Stop the Feeling!\" \u2013 Max Martin, Shellback and Justin Timberlake\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://variety.com/2017/music/news/world-soundtrack-academy-award-nominees-2017-1202526811/ |title=\u2018La La Land,\u2019 \u2018Stranger Things\u2019 Among 2017 World Soundtrack Award Nominees |date=August 21, 2017 |work=Variety |access-date=September 15, 2017}}</ref>\n|}\n\n*Regarding music award shows, only film-related categories are included on this list.\n\n==Franchise==\n''DreamWorks Trolls: The Experience'' was the first of multiple mobile pop-up attractions [[Feld Entertainment]] and [[Universal Pictures|Universal Brand Development]] had agreed to develop in April 2018.<ref name=\"ks\">{{cite news|last1=Whyte|first1=Alexandra|title=Universal, Feld develop Trolls interactive attraction|url=http://kidscreen.com/2018/05/01/universal-feld-entertainment-develop-trolls-attraction/|accessdate=May 1, 2018|work=Kidscreen|publisher=Brunico Communications Ltd.|date=May 1, 2018}}</ref> The pop-up attraction opened in [[New York City]] on October 22, 2018.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Gross |first1=Arlene |title=New 'DreamWorks Trolls' event coming to NYC |url=https://www.newsday.com/lifestyle/family/dreamworks-trolls-experience-new-york-1.20213760 |accessdate=August 15, 2018 |work=Newsday |date=July 31, 2018 }}</ref>\n\n{{Anchor|Trolls World Tour}}\n\n=== Sequel ===\n{{main|Trolls World Tour}}\nOn February 28, 2017, [[Universal Pictures]], the studio's new distributor and parent company since 2016, and [[DreamWorks Animation]] announced that a sequel titled ''Trolls 2'' would be released on April 10, 2020, with Kendrick and Timberlake reprising their roles of Poppy and Branch as well as Aibel and Berger returning to write the script.<ref name=VarietyTrolls2020>{{cite news|last1=Kroll|first1=Justin|title=Universal DreamWorks Animation Announces \u2018Trolls 2\u2019; Sets for April 10, 2020|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/trolls-2-announced-april-2020-dreamworks-animation-1201998983/|accessdate=March 5, 2017|work=Variety|date=February 28, 2017}}</ref> On October 4, 2017, the release date for the sequel was moved up to February 14, 2020, as ''[[Fast & Furious 9]]'' took its original April 10, 2020 slot. Along with the new release date, it was announced that Dohrn will be returning to direct and Shay will return to produce the sequel. On December 6, 2017, the film was pushed back to an April 17, 2020 release. On March 4, 2020, ''[[No Time to Die]]'' got delayed, so the film was pushed to an April 10, 2020 release again.<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2017/10/fast-furious-9-easter-weekend-2020-release-date-trolls-2-valentines-day-opening-2020-1202181866/|title=\u2018Fast & Furious 9\u2019 Drives To Easter Weekend 2020; DreamWorks Animation's \u2018Trolls 2\u2019 Eyes Valentine's Day. |last=D'Alessandro|first=Anthony|date=October 4, 2017|website=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=November 7, 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2018, it was confirmed that [[Sam Rockwell]], [[Chance the Rapper]], [[Anthony Ramos (actor)|Anthony Ramos]], [[Karan Soni]], [[Flula Borg]], and [[Jamie Dornan]] joined the cast. Corden, Icona Pop, Funches, Stefani and Nayyar will also reprise their roles.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://deadline.com/2018/05/sam-rockwell-chance-the-rapper-trolls-2-animated-movie-1202387559/ |title=Sam Rockwell, Chance The Rapper Join DreamWorks\u2019 \u2018Trolls 2\u2019|last=Busch|first=Anita |date=May 10, 2018 |website=Deadline Hollywood|access-date=May 10, 2018}}</ref> In October 2018, it was confirmed that [[Kelly Clarkson]] had joined the cast, and will perform an original song.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://deadline.com/2018/10/kelly-clarkson-trolls-2-perform-original-song-1202476507/|title=Kelly Clarkson & Reece McCreless Joins \u2018Trolls 2\u2019 & Will Perform Original Song|magazine=Deadline Hollywood|last=N'Duka|first1=Amanda|last2=D'Alessandro|first2=Anthony|date=October 4, 2018|accessdate=October 5, 2018}}</ref>\n\nA new title for the sequel, ''Trolls World Tour'', was announced in June 2018.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/behind-screen/emmys-trolls-holiday-lights-up-animation-race-1119149 |title=Emmys: Trolls Light Up Animation Race With Holiday Special |date=June 12, 2018 |website=The Hollywood Reporter}}</ref> In May 2017, podcasters [[Justin McElroy|Justin]], [[Travis McElroy|Travis]] and [[Griffin McElroy]] began campaigning for roles in the film via a podcast titled \"The McElroy Brothers Will Be in Trolls 2\" (later renamed \"The McElroy Brothers Will Be in Trolls: World Tour\" after the sequel's subtitle was revealed).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://trolls2.libsyn.com|title=The McElroy Brothers Will Be in Trolls 2|website=trolls2.libsyn.com|access-date=16 September 2018}}</ref> Following the podcast's popularity, DreamWorks confirmed in September 2018 that the McElroy brothers would make cameo appearances in ''World Tour''.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2018/09/trolls-world-tour-mcelroy-brothers-casting |title=The Unbelievable True Story of How Three Podcasters Trolled Their Way into Trolls 2 |last=Bradley |first=Laura |date=September 11, 2018 |website=[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]] |access-date=September 11, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2019, along with promotional posters, new cast members have been announced, which include: [[J Balvin]], [[Mary J. Blige]], [[Rachel Bloom]], [[George Clinton (musician)|George Clinton]], [[Ester Dean]] and [[Gustavo Dudamel]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Sarto |first1=Dan |title=DreamWorks Animation Reveals 21 Posters and Cast for \u2018Trolls World Tour\u2019 |url=https://www.awn.com/news/dreamworks-animation-reveals-21-posters-and-cast-trolls-world-tour |accessdate=19 June 2019 |work=Animation World Network |date=19 June 2019 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n===Television special===\n{{Main|Trolls Holiday}}\n''Trolls Holiday'' is a half-hour<ref name=NBCTrollsSpecial /> television special that aired on November 24, 2017 on [[NBC]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Connelly|first1=Brendon|title=Frozen, Trolls getting new TV specials|url=https://www.denofgeek.com/uk/movies/transformers/47678/frozen-trolls-getting-new-tv-specials|publisher=Den of Geek!|accessdate=March 5, 2017|date=March 3, 2017}}</ref> Set after the film, Poppy realizes that the Bergens have no holidays to celebrate. She enlists Branch and their friends (the Snack Pack) to show their best friend Bridget and other Bergens the importance of holidays. Most of the original cast (including Kendrick, Timberlake, Deschanel, Mintz-Plasse, Corden, Funches, Nayyar and Dohrn) all reprise their roles from the film. The likely-Christmas Special is also directed by Crawford and written by Josh Bycel & Jonathan Fener with music by Jeff Morrow.<ref name=NBCTrollsSpecial>{{cite web|title=Trolls Holiday|url=http://www.nbc.com/trolls-holiday?nbc=1|publisher=NBC|accessdate=May 20, 2017}}</ref> Its soundtrack album that features seven songs was released on October 27, 2017.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.amazon.com/Trolls-Holiday-Various/dp/B0761FKYBM |title=TROLLS Holiday |publisher=Amazon.com |accessdate=October 20, 2017}}</ref> It is now available on Netflix and on DVD by [[Universal Pictures Home Entertainment]]. The bonus features of the DVD also include one episode of ''[[Spirit Riding Free]]'' and two of ''[[Home: Adventures with Tip & Oh]]''.\n\n===Animated series===\n{{Main|Trolls: The Beat Goes On!}}\nA 52-episode animated series based on the film, entitled ''Trolls: The Beat Goes On!'' that airs on [[Netflix]] premiered on January 19, 2018 and ran for 8 seasons.<ref name=\"FOXBTrollsEverywhere\">{{cite web|last1=Schwartzel|first1=Erich|title=Trolls Everywhere: NBCUniversal Aims to Use Parent Comcast's Reach to Spawn a Franchise|url=http://www.foxbusiness.com/features/2017/10/10/trolls-everywhere-nbcuniversal-aims-to-use-parent-comcasts-reach-to-spawn-franchise.html|publisher=Fox Business|accessdate=October 13, 2017|date=October 10, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/bwwtv/article/Justin-Timberlake-Anna-Kendrick-Set-for-NBC-Animated-Musical-Special-DREAMWORKS-TROLLS-HOLIDAY-20171017|title=Justin Timberlake, Anna Kendrick Set for NBC Animated Musical Special DREAMWORKS TROLLS HOLIDAY|website=Broadwayworld.com|accessdate=November 7, 2017}}</ref> The show stars [[Amanda Leighton]] as Poppy, [[Skylar Astin]] as Branch, and Funches who is reprising his role as Cooper, and Dohrn reprising his role as Cloud Guy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.toonbarn.com/dreamworks/trolls-beat-goes-netflix-series-gets-first-image-tv-special-dated/|title=Trolls: The Beat Goes On Netflix series gets first image|date=October 21, 2017|website=Toonbarn.com|accessdate=November 7, 2017}}</ref>\n\nAnother series titled ''TrollsTopia'' will be released on the upcoming streaming service [[Peacock (streaming service)|Peacock]].<ref>https://deadline.com/feature/peacock-tv-nbc-universal-streaming-service-1202832718/</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n{{Commons category|Trolls (film)}}\n*{{Official website|https://www.dreamworks.com/movies/trolls}}\n*[http://dreamworkstrollsparty.com Dreamworks Trolls Party]\n*{{IMDb title|1679335}}\n*{{bcdb title|144845}}\n*{{mojo title|trolls}}\n*{{Rotten Tomatoes|trolls}}\n*{{metacritic film|trolls}}\n*{{AllMovie title|571273}}\n\n{{Trolls}}\n{{DreamWorks animated films}}\n{{Mike Mitchell}}\n{{Portal bar|Cartoon|Animation}}\n\n[[Category:2016 films]]\n[[Category:Trolls (film)| ]]\n[[Category:2016 3D films]]\n[[Category:2016 computer-animated films]]\n[[Category:2010s American animated films]]\n[[Category:2010s fantasy-comedy films]]\n[[Category:2010s musical comedy films]]\n[[Category:2010s children's animated films]]\n[[Category:20th Century Fox animated films]]\n[[Category:American 3D films]]\n[[Category:American children's animated fantasy films]]\n[[Category:American children's animated comedy films]]\n[[Category:American computer-animated films]]\n[[Category:American fantasy-comedy films]]\n[[Category:American musical comedy films]]\n[[Category:American romantic comedy films]]\n[[Category:American romantic musical films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:Films set in 1996]]\n[[Category:Films set in 2016]]\n[[Category:Animated comedy films]]\n[[Category:Animated musical films]]\n[[Category:Animated buddy films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:Films about trolls]]\n[[Category:Films based on toys]]\n[[Category:Jukebox musical films]]\n[[Category:DreamWorks Animation animated films]]